<table border="0" cellpadding="5" width="550" cellspacing="5" height="400" >
<tr valign="top" height="400" >
<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; bEditID:r3st1; color:#000000; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<p class="MsoNormal" style=""><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Hi {!Contact.FirstName},<br></font><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><br>We are getting in touch today as you recently purchased an insurance policy with us and opted to pay by Direct Debit through Close Brothers Premium Finance.<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br>As part of Close Brothers’ ongoing Anti-Money Laundering requirements, they are required to identify all of their customers. Unfortunately, they have been unable to do this through their automated process, and have therefore asked if you can </span><b style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">please provide a copy of one of the following documents</b><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">:</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""></p><ul><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Passport (valid and in date)</font></li><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Valid Full/Provisional Photocard Driving License</font></li><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">National ID Card</font></li></ul><p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Please could you <b>send the copy to us via email at your earliest convenience</b> so we can pass these to Close Brothers’ to complete their checks.&nbsp; Either <b>a photograph or scanned copy would be acceptable, please do not send originals</b>.<br></font><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br>Unfortunately, </span><b style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">if Close Brothers are unable to complete their checks they may cancel your loan</b><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"> which would leave you with an outstanding balance which, if remained unpaid, could ultimately lead to debt collection proceedings.<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br>If you have any further questions, please feel free to reply to this email, or give us a call on </span><b style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">01242 808740 (option 4)</b><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">.<br></span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><br>Kind regards,<br></span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><br>{!User.FirstName}<br></span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">Customer Accounts Team<br></span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><br>E: customersupport@kingsbridge.co.uk<br></span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">T: 01242 808 740</span></p>]]></td>
</tr>
</table>